HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 913
By Littleton
A RESOLUTION to recognize and commend the outstanding work
of Jobs for America's Graduates in Tennessee
and to highlight the exceptional return on the
State's investment in this vital program.
WHEREAS, Jobs for America's Graduates Tennessee (JAGTN), an affiliate of the
national Jobs for America's Graduates organization, is a nonprofit dedicated to guiding high
school students toward graduation while equipping them with essential skills for employability,
postsecondary education, and lifelong success; and
WHEREAS, founded in 1981 under Governor Lamar Alexander and initially exclusively
state-funded, JAGTN is now one of the longest-serving affiliates of Jobs for America's
Graduates; since 2013, it has expanded through diverse partnerships with school districts,
private businesses, and regional nonprofits to serve forty-two schools across thirty counties; and
WHEREAS, in order to fulfill its mission, JAGTN empowers students with the tools to
excel in the workforce, education, and life and tracks graduates for one full year after high
school to ensure they remain on a path toward career or college; and
WHEREAS, the program has demonstrated remarkable outcomes, including a 99.8
percent graduation rate for its students in 2025, far surpassing the statewide average of 90
percent, and securing $59.6 million in postsecondary scholarships for the Class of 2025; and
WHEREAS, JAGTN participants achieve 80 percent positive outcomes, such as
employment, postsecondary enrollment, or military service, with 60 percent entering the
workforce—60 percent of whom secure full-time positions—and show significant improvements
in GPA, attendance, self-esteem, and reductions in barriers and discipline referrals; and
HJR0913
011982
- 1 -

WHEREAS, the program's impact extends to broader societal benefits, fostering
confident graduates who become productive citizens and leaders in Tennessee's communities
and economy; and
WHEREAS, JAGTN delivers an extraordinary return on investment for the State of
Tennessee, yielding $25.50 in economic benefits for every $1.00 invested through enhanced
productivity, reduced social costs, and increased workforce readiness; and
WHEREAS, this impressive return on investment underscores the program's efficiency
and value, making it a model public-private partnership that amplifies State resources while
addressing critical needs in education and workforce development; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we hereby recognize and commend Jobs for America's Graduates
Tennessee for its exemplary work in transforming the lives of Tennessee's high school students
and delivering substantial returns on the State's investment.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
